{"info": {"author": "Ivan", "author_email": "ivan.vershigora@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: POSIX :: Linux", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# SomeBar\n\nSimple taskbar indicator for Unity inspired by [AnyBar](https://github.com/tonsky/AnyBar) (basically it is a clone of AnyBar)\n\nTested on Ubuntu 18.04 with Unity and Ubuntu GNOME\n\n<img src=\"screenshot_unity.png?raw=true\" />\n\n<img src=\"screenshot_ubuntugnome.png?raw=true\" />\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\npip3 install somebar\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nto run somebar just execute in console\n```sh\nsomebar\n```\n\nsomebar is controlled via UDP port (1738 by default). Send it a message and it will change a color:\n\n```sh\necho -n \"black\" | nc -4u -w0 localhost 1738\n```\n\nFollowing commands change color:\n\n\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/white@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `white`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/red@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `red`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/orange@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `orange`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/yellow@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `yellow`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/green@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `green`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/cyan@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `cyan`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/blue@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `blue`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/purple@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `purple`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/black@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `black`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/question@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `question`\n<img src=\"somebar_icons/exclamation@2x.png?raw=true\" width=19 /> `exclamation`\n\nAnd one special command forces somebar to quit: `quit`\n\n## Running multiple instances\n\nYou can run several instances of somebar as long as they listen on different ports. Use `-p` or `--port` command line argument to change port:\n\n```sh\nsomebar -p 1738\nsomebar -p 1739\nsomebar -p 1740\n```\n\n## Custom images\n\nsomebar can use user-local images if you put them under `~/.somebar` or `~/.AnyBar`. E.g. if you have `~/.AnyBar/square@2x.png` present, send `square` to 1738 and it will be displayed.\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "https://github.com/limpbrains/somebar/tarball/0.0.7", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/limpbrains/somebar", "keywords": "AnyBar,somebar,taskbar,indicator", "license": "MIT License", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "somebar", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/somebar/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/somebar/", "project_urls": {"Download": "https://github.com/limpbrains/somebar/tarball/0.0.7", "Homepage": "https://github.com/limpbrains/somebar"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/somebar/0.0.7/", "requires_dist": null, "requires_python": "", "summary": "Simple taskbar widget that displays color dot or custom icon", "version": "0.0.7", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p># SomeBar</p>\n<p>Simple taskbar indicator for Unity inspired by [AnyBar](<a href=\"https://github.com/tonsky/AnyBar\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://github.com/tonsky/AnyBar</a>) (basically it is a clone of AnyBar)</p>\n<p>Tested on Ubuntu 18.04 with Unity and Ubuntu GNOME</p>\n<p>&lt;img src=\u201dscreenshot_unity.png?raw=true\u201d /&gt;</p>\n<p>&lt;img src=\u201dscreenshot_ubuntugnome.png?raw=true\u201d /&gt;</p>\n<p>## Install</p>\n<p><tt>`sh\npip3 install somebar\n`</tt></p>\n<p>## Usage</p>\n<p>to run somebar just execute in console\n<tt>`sh\nsomebar\n`</tt></p>\n<p>somebar is controlled via UDP port (1738 by default). Send it a message and it will change a color:</p>\n<p><tt>`sh\necho <span class=\"pre\">-n</span> \"black\" | nc <span class=\"pre\">-4u</span> <span class=\"pre\">-w0</span> localhost 1738\n`</tt></p>\n<p>Following commands change color:</p>\n<p>&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/white%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/white<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>white</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/red%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/red<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>red</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/orange%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/orange<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>orange</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/yellow%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/yellow<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>yellow</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/green%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/green<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>green</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/cyan%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/cyan<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>cyan</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/blue%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/blue<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>blue</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/purple%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/purple<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>purple</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/black%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/black<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>black</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/question%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/question<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>question</cite>\n&lt;img src=\u201d<a href=\"mailto:somebar_icons/exclamation%402x.png?raw=true\">somebar_icons/exclamation<span>@</span>2x<span>.</span>png?raw=true</a>\u201d width=19 /&gt; <cite>exclamation</cite></p>\n<p>And one special command forces somebar to quit: <cite>quit</cite></p>\n<p>## Running multiple instances</p>\n<p>You can run several instances of somebar as long as they listen on different ports. Use <cite>-p</cite> or <cite>\u2013port</cite> command line argument to change port:</p>\n<p><tt>`sh\nsomebar <span class=\"pre\">-p</span> 1738\nsomebar <span class=\"pre\">-p</span> 1739\nsomebar <span class=\"pre\">-p</span> 1740\n`</tt></p>\n<p>## Custom images</p>\n<p>somebar can use user-local images if you put them under <cite>~/.somebar</cite> or <cite>~/.AnyBar</cite>. E.g. if you have <cite>~/.AnyBar/square@2x.png</cite> present, send <cite>square</cite> to 1738 and it will be displayed.</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 4055387, "releases": {"0.0.2": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "77b8082a3db1a1350d7913651c027af9", "sha256": "60442ace9b0166973ffb1d7541df6bf3c6f7a63f92aa8b1441f3df41d5b2ef84"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "somebar-0.0.2.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "77b8082a3db1a1350d7913651c027af9", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 39189, "upload_time": "2015-04-07T13:39:52", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2015-04-07T13:39:52.686075Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/cd/56/5c56416ea1de5bd9f1c41e8f04b67cf8ac54bc241ba98bba09fa7aae2874/somebar-0.0.2.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "0.0.3": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "50333b158dfe517103dd19bc4966dfef", "sha256": "b53dd9d77f499a590543ee36a85c9a8fd6f033b1c304548f739ada06df0f63e9"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "somebar-0.0.3.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "50333b158dfe517103dd19bc4966dfef", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 39142, "upload_time": "2015-04-07T13:50:16", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2015-04-07T13:50:16.009396Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/d9/75/7ebf9dd46c3eb53